title: Ella Fitzgerald - Clap Hands, Here Comes Charlie! (1961) RESEED
description:
MP3/320kbps

Opening with Dizzy Gillespie&#039;s classic "Night in Tunisia," which features some outstanding scatting, CLAP HANDS, 

HERE COMES CHARLIE continues in that bop-oriented vein, with versions of "Stella By Starlight" and Monk&#039;s "&#039;Round 

Midnight." The highest point on the album, though, is a stunning, stripped-down version of "Cry Me a River." The three 

bonus tracks, recorded during these sessions, are very good, but not revelatory, though the saucy "I Got a Guy" is 

swinging fun.

Personnel: 
Ella Fitzgerald (vocals)
Lou Levy (piano)
Herb Ellis (guitar)
Joe Mondragon (bass)
Stan Levey (drums)

Recorded in Los Angeles, California on June 22-23, 1961.
